Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop the potatoes on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat in the oil, then roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(finely chopped, stalks and all), zest and halve the @lemon{½}(zested and halved) and roughly chop the @chorizo{60%g}(roughly chopped). Pop the chorizo, @Panko breadcrumbs{10%g} and olive oil for the crumb into a #bowl{}. Add the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}, lemon zest, half the parsley and a grind of pepper. Mix together.

Put three-quarters of the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} into a bowl (set aside). Line a baking tray with #baking paper{} and lay on the @cod fillets{2}. Spread the remaining mayo on top of the cod pieces, then spoon over the chorizo crumb. Push it down to ensure it sticks (don't worry if some of it falls off). Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until the crumbs are golden and the fish cooked, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after touching raw fish!

> The cod is cooked when opaque all the way through.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{½}(peeled and grated) with a #garlic press{}. Put the garlic in the bowl with the mayo and remaining parsley. Squeeze in a little of the lemon juice, season with salt and pepper and mix everything together. Leave to the side.

> TIP: Use less garlic if you don't love raw garlic.

Chop off and discard the bottom 2cm of the @asparagus{200%g}. Halve the asparagus widthways. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} over medium heat. Once hot, add the asparagus and season with salt and pepper. Fry for ~{1%minute}, then add a splash of water and cover the pan with a #lid{} or some #tin foil{}. Immediately turn the heat to medium and steam until the asparagus is tender, ~{4-6%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Serve the cod on plates with the potatoes and asparagus alongside. Add a spoonful of the aioli. Chop any remaining lemon into wedges and serve alongside. Enjoy!